snippet.textDisplay: Personal taste: Too salty. Since Jiff PB has quite a bit of salt and you’re using Baking Soda (although not technically salt but still tastes salty) I’d recommend using less table salt and even none. Just texted with my son who I’d love to have make these for me. He did! He lives two day’s drive from me. Darn! ☹️ Didn’t help except he’s the one who warned me that the 1/4 tsp salt was too much. Hard to shift down from so little. Again, if you’re sensitive to salt, you may get away by using no table salt. If you like salty, go for it! From my son and his wife: “These are darned good! Save yourselves and just send us more milk!”

snippet.textDisplay:
Alton Browns peanut butter cookies.
1 Egg
1 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup Peanut butter
1/2 brown sugar
1/2 cup gran sugar

Preheat oven 350
Mix peanut butter, sugars
Add egg, baking soda, salt, and vanilla extract until smooth.

Make 1 oz, by volume, balls of dough and have enough space between them. THEY SPREAD. Lick remaining dough when no one is looking. Make cross marks with fork and Bake in sheet pans for 10 minutes. Turn half way into the baking time. Let cool and enjoy.
snippet.textOriginal:
Alton Browns peanut butter cookies. 
1 Egg
1 tsp baking soda 
1/4 tsp salt 
1 tsp vanilla extract 
1 cup Peanut butter 
1/2 brown sugar
1/2 cup gran sugar
 
Preheat oven 350
Mix peanut butter, sugars
Add egg, baking soda, salt, and vanilla extract until smooth. 

Make 1 oz, by volume, balls of dough and have enough space between them. THEY SPREAD. Lick remaining dough when no one is looking. Make cross marks with fork and Bake in sheet pans for 10 minutes. Turn half way into the baking time. Let cool and enjoy.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Alton,
Thank you for this nice, fairly simple cookie recipe, and easy to follow instructions.
Also, I fondly remember how you used to say, when you still had Good Eats, "Oh bother!!".
Well, guess what?! Tonight, when I was watching the old black-n-white episodes of Andy Griffith, there was a guest appearance of the actor that voices Winnie the Pooh!! He's the one who says, "Oh bother!". (Sterling Holloway).
My daughter noticed him right away, she exclaimed, "that's Winnie the Pooh!!!"
We watch all the old reruns of the old shows every night.
Check out MeTV channel, Antenna TV, and CoziTV. All of these channels have the old cherished favorites. You and Elizabeth can watch all these, look on the guide, instead of drinking yourself into oblivion, or manically making video, after video!! Lol.
Don't forget Perry Mason, Twilight Zone, Alfred Hitchcock, Mannix, Cannon, Barnaby Jones, Dragnet, Adam 12, etc.

At night, we watch Andy Griffith, Gomer Pyle, Green Acres, Hogun's Heros, Perry Mason, ....
In the morning, it's I Love Lucy, The Beverly Hillbillys, My Three Sons, Leave It to Beaver, ....
That Girl, on AntennaTV, and Charlies Angels, and Bionic Woman, don't forget, Father Knows Best, at 6am-7am.
And the original Starsky and Hutch, every Saturday afternoon, on CoziTV.

"And just one more thing", (Columbo)

*enjoy. Lol. 😀❤
